===Etymology===
{{Han etym}}
According to STEDT & {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*kwar||hole, orifice; innards}}.
*Inside Chinese, cognate with {{och-l|貫|id=2}} "to go through, to pierce";
*Outside Chinese, cognate with {{cog|bca|tr=khuɑ̱̃²¹|t=cave, hole}}, {{cog|lus|khuar}} ~ {{m|lus|khur||hole}}, {{cog|my|ဂူ||cave}} (however, see there for alternative etymologies), etc.

